WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.388 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:03.388 --> 00:00:13.570 align:middle line:90%


00:00:13.570 --> 00:00:18.130 align:middle line:84%
>> Since childhood, I've
been very attracted to water.

00:00:18.130 --> 00:00:21.130 align:middle line:84%
I grew up with a swimming
pool in the backyard

00:00:21.130 --> 00:00:24.010 align:middle line:84%
and we had a family
boat, so it was always

00:00:24.010 --> 00:00:26.800 align:middle line:84%
about exploring the
ocean, basically.

00:00:26.800 --> 00:00:28.300 align:middle line:84%
And my parents
wanted me to be safe,

00:00:28.300 --> 00:00:32.780 align:middle line:84%
so even from a stage of being
a baby, I learned swimming,

00:00:32.780 --> 00:00:35.770 align:middle line:84%
both with my mother,
but also professionally.

00:00:35.770 --> 00:00:38.860 align:middle line:84%
And that led into
competitive swimming

00:00:38.860 --> 00:00:41.740 align:middle line:90%
and freediving eventually.

00:00:41.740 --> 00:00:45.280 align:middle line:84%
So it's been always something
that that's been like a hobby

00:00:45.280 --> 00:00:47.584 align:middle line:84%
and then turned
into a profession.

00:00:47.584 --> 00:00:50.888 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:50.888 --> 00:00:54.528 align:middle line:90%


00:00:54.528 --> 00:00:56.320 align:middle line:84%
I think what happened
to me-- in freediving

00:00:56.320 --> 00:00:58.150 align:middle line:84%
was going from
competitive free diving

00:00:58.150 --> 00:01:01.690 align:middle line:84%
and becoming a full-time
freediving world champion,

00:01:01.690 --> 00:01:04.900 align:middle line:84%
I realized that you didn't
have a big impact, really,

00:01:04.900 --> 00:01:06.400 align:middle line:90%
because it's a very small sport.

00:01:06.400 --> 00:01:09.670 align:middle line:84%
It's a beautiful sport
and it's a great journey,

00:01:09.670 --> 00:01:11.870 align:middle line:90%
but it's still very limited.

00:01:11.870 --> 00:01:14.530 align:middle line:84%
So I wanted to reach
a greater audience,

00:01:14.530 --> 00:01:19.690 align:middle line:84%
and when I passed the 20-minute
limit breath hold-- so in 2010,

00:01:19.690 --> 00:01:21.920 align:middle line:84%
I was the first person on
this planet to surpass that

00:01:21.920 --> 00:01:22.720 align:middle line:90%
barrier--

00:01:22.720 --> 00:01:24.910 align:middle line:84%
I held my breath for
20 minutes, 10 seconds

00:01:24.910 --> 00:01:28.920 align:middle line:84%
because I like to show that
dedication and perfectionism.

00:01:28.920 --> 00:01:31.750 align:middle line:84%
So on April 1, to
make it a bit funny,

00:01:31.750 --> 00:01:34.270 align:middle line:84%
I held my breath in a shark
tank for 20 minutes, 10 seconds.

00:01:34.270 --> 00:01:37.210 align:middle line:84%
And that showed me a new
way of using my sport

00:01:37.210 --> 00:01:39.070 align:middle line:90%
to helping more people.

00:01:39.070 --> 00:01:41.320 align:middle line:84%
And then I went on to do the
22-minutes Guinness World

00:01:41.320 --> 00:01:43.820 align:middle line:84%
Record, the current official
Guinness World Record.

00:01:43.820 --> 00:01:47.350 align:middle line:84%
I also did 250 feet
under ice in Speedos,

00:01:47.350 --> 00:01:52.690 align:middle line:84%
and that also seemed to start
almost a new trend in health

00:01:52.690 --> 00:01:55.120 align:middle line:84%
and Viking swimming,
we call it--

00:01:55.120 --> 00:01:58.600 align:middle line:84%
so go and swim when
it's cold, in ice water,

00:01:58.600 --> 00:02:00.740 align:middle line:84%
like they do in
Russia and Finland.

00:02:00.740 --> 00:02:04.330 align:middle line:84%
And there's a whole
new movement now,

00:02:04.330 --> 00:02:09.430 align:middle line:84%
understanding all the benefits
and the energy-raising benefits

00:02:09.430 --> 00:02:11.470 align:middle line:90%
from swimming under ice.

00:02:11.470 --> 00:02:13.395 align:middle line:84%
Also did 500 feet
with a monofin,

00:02:13.395 --> 00:02:15.520 align:middle line:84%
and those were all official
Guinness World Records,

00:02:15.520 --> 00:02:17.312 align:middle line:84%
and it was on a show
for Discovery Channel.

00:02:17.312 --> 00:02:20.680 align:middle line:84%
So that reached a big
audience, and in that, I

00:02:20.680 --> 00:02:23.860 align:middle line:84%
reached my goal of getting the
message out that breathing,

00:02:23.860 --> 00:02:26.722 align:middle line:84%
breathwork, and linking
that with your mind really

00:02:26.722 --> 00:02:28.930 align:middle line:84%
can have a tremendous impact
on both your performance

00:02:28.930 --> 00:02:30.990 align:middle line:90%
but also your daily health.

00:02:30.990 --> 00:02:34.350 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:02:34.350 --> 00:02:37.710 align:middle line:90%


00:02:37.710 --> 00:02:41.060 align:middle line:84%
Well, one of the reasons
for doing the "Speedo dive,"

00:02:41.060 --> 00:02:44.530 align:middle line:84%
[CHUCKLES] as we call it--
it's been nicknamed swimming

00:02:44.530 --> 00:02:47.740 align:middle line:84%
basically naked under
ice in Greenland--

00:02:47.740 --> 00:02:53.300 align:middle line:84%
was to reach, for me,
the epitome of my career

00:02:53.300 --> 00:02:56.140 align:middle line:84%
and freediving
and use everything

00:02:56.140 --> 00:03:00.430 align:middle line:84%
I've learned to put it
into a kind of masterpiece.

00:03:00.430 --> 00:03:02.060 align:middle line:84%
And that's why we
chose Greenland.

00:03:02.060 --> 00:03:04.720 align:middle line:84%
We had incredible support
from the local community,

00:03:04.720 --> 00:03:07.120 align:middle line:84%
from the people behind
the scenes shooting this,

00:03:07.120 --> 00:03:11.050 align:middle line:84%
and it was truly like swimming
on a different planet.

00:03:11.050 --> 00:03:13.720 align:middle line:84%
Like when you see movies and
the best Hollywood productions,

00:03:13.720 --> 00:03:15.640 align:middle line:90%
this was like being there live.

00:03:15.640 --> 00:03:17.680 align:middle line:84%
So even though I swim
with my eyes closed

00:03:17.680 --> 00:03:18.790 align:middle line:90%
and I'm very focused--

00:03:18.790 --> 00:03:21.880 align:middle line:84%
I'm in a different
mental state--

00:03:21.880 --> 00:03:24.820 align:middle line:84%
we still had the
training dives and I also

00:03:24.820 --> 00:03:26.260 align:middle line:84%
peek sometimes to
know where I am

00:03:26.260 --> 00:03:28.300 align:middle line:90%
so I'm not getting off course.

00:03:28.300 --> 00:03:31.870 align:middle line:84%
But that experience of being
in this pristine environment,

00:03:31.870 --> 00:03:34.660 align:middle line:90%
its crushing beauty--

00:03:34.660 --> 00:03:38.433 align:middle line:84%
and Greenland is truly stunning
because you feel so small,

00:03:38.433 --> 00:03:39.850 align:middle line:84%
so it also puts
you in your place.

00:03:39.850 --> 00:03:40.660 align:middle line:90%
You know, you're a nobody.

00:03:40.660 --> 00:03:42.370 align:middle line:84%
You're just doing some
Guinness World Records.

00:03:42.370 --> 00:03:43.240 align:middle line:90%
Who cares?

00:03:43.240 --> 00:03:44.680 align:middle line:90%
It's like-- really.

00:03:44.680 --> 00:03:45.760 align:middle line:90%
It's all about nature.

00:03:45.760 --> 00:03:48.100 align:middle line:84%
And this deep connection
I think, also,

00:03:48.100 --> 00:03:50.140 align:middle line:90%
is what connected with people.

00:03:50.140 --> 00:03:52.480 align:middle line:84%
Because it's true that it's
difficult for many people

00:03:52.480 --> 00:03:52.930 align:middle line:90%
to understand.

00:03:52.930 --> 00:03:53.930 align:middle line:90%
What is this freediving?

00:03:53.930 --> 00:03:56.050 align:middle line:84%
And it's kind of crazy,
holding your breath.

00:03:56.050 --> 00:03:58.210 align:middle line:90%
And some people go on a machine.

00:03:58.210 --> 00:04:01.955 align:middle line:84%
Sometimes they dive just
a long distance in a pool.

00:04:01.955 --> 00:04:03.580 align:middle line:84%
There's also something
extremely boring

00:04:03.580 --> 00:04:06.340 align:middle line:84%
called static-- the one where I
hold my breath for 22 minutes.

00:04:06.340 --> 00:04:07.550 align:middle line:90%
Really boring.

00:04:07.550 --> 00:04:09.550 align:middle line:84%
But there is a lot of
stuff going on, of course,

00:04:09.550 --> 00:04:12.140 align:middle line:84%
mentally and
spiritually behind that.

00:04:12.140 --> 00:04:15.190 align:middle line:84%
But it's hard for people to
connect to this experience.

00:04:15.190 --> 00:04:17.709 align:middle line:84%
But when you see
somebody dive under ice,

00:04:17.709 --> 00:04:20.350 align:middle line:84%
there will be some reaction,
like oh, that's cold,

00:04:20.350 --> 00:04:23.460 align:middle line:84%
or that's amazing, or
wow, that's beautiful.

00:04:23.460 --> 00:04:25.210 align:middle line:84%
I've never seen images
from under the ice.

00:04:25.210 --> 00:04:27.130 align:middle line:84%
So I think that
record brought a lot

00:04:27.130 --> 00:04:30.430 align:middle line:84%
of extra dimensions
of beauty and nature

00:04:30.430 --> 00:04:32.253 align:middle line:90%
into people's living rooms.

00:04:32.253 --> 00:04:35.564 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:04:35.564 --> 00:04:39.480 align:middle line:90%


00:04:39.480 --> 00:04:41.850 align:middle line:84%
The cold is always a
challenge because you will

00:04:41.850 --> 00:04:44.940 align:middle line:90%
die if you're not prepared.

00:04:44.940 --> 00:04:48.630 align:middle line:84%
Doctors always talk about
brain freeze or stroke.

00:04:48.630 --> 00:04:52.730 align:middle line:84%
So your heart can
basically stop if there

00:04:52.730 --> 00:04:55.770 align:middle line:84%
is too big of a shock for the
difference in temperature.

00:04:55.770 --> 00:04:57.320 align:middle line:90%
But I had prepared well.

00:04:57.320 --> 00:04:59.430 align:middle line:84%
I had done this Guinness
World Record before.

00:04:59.430 --> 00:05:01.660 align:middle line:84%
I actually was the
record holder already.

00:05:01.660 --> 00:05:03.750 align:middle line:84%
So it was not about
setting a new record.

00:05:03.750 --> 00:05:06.240 align:middle line:84%
It was more about
making the perfect dive.

00:05:06.240 --> 00:05:09.070 align:middle line:84%
So it was a beautiful
dive and elegant,

00:05:09.070 --> 00:05:14.370 align:middle line:84%
and it was actually to show
the serenity of nature.

00:05:14.370 --> 00:05:16.710 align:middle line:84%
And we couldn't find a
better place than Greenland

00:05:16.710 --> 00:05:18.570 align:middle line:84%
to do this-- swimming
under the ice.

00:05:18.570 --> 00:05:19.612 align:middle line:90%
But it's also about luck.

00:05:19.612 --> 00:05:20.412 align:middle line:90%
You know?

00:05:20.412 --> 00:05:22.110 align:middle line:84%
We did not know the
conditions because I

00:05:22.110 --> 00:05:24.840 align:middle line:84%
was the first human being
ever to dive in that lake.

00:05:24.840 --> 00:05:28.470 align:middle line:84%
That experience alone-- being
the first human being on this

00:05:28.470 --> 00:05:31.800 align:middle line:84%
planet with, soon I
think, 8 billion people--

00:05:31.800 --> 00:05:33.840 align:middle line:84%
to be the first to
touch that water,

00:05:33.840 --> 00:05:35.697 align:middle line:84%
it was like the
holy grail for me.

00:05:35.697 --> 00:05:39.176 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:05:39.176 --> 00:05:44.650 align:middle line:90%


00:05:44.650 --> 00:05:47.860 align:middle line:84%
The 22-minute dive was
really a wonderful dive.

00:05:47.860 --> 00:05:52.480 align:middle line:84%
It was a tough dive, pushing
me to my absolute limit.

00:05:52.480 --> 00:05:54.880 align:middle line:84%
But I had trained for the
dive, and I really, really

00:05:54.880 --> 00:05:56.260 align:middle line:90%
wanted it to be successful.

00:05:56.260 --> 00:05:59.920 align:middle line:90%


00:05:59.920 --> 00:06:02.337 align:middle line:84%
You breathe oxygen before,
just so people get the picture,

00:06:02.337 --> 00:06:03.962 align:middle line:84%
but you still have
to hold your breath.

00:06:03.962 --> 00:06:06.340 align:middle line:84%
So the most difficult thing
about holding your breath

00:06:06.340 --> 00:06:09.250 align:middle line:84%
is not lacking oxygen.
Well, then at one point,

00:06:09.250 --> 00:06:10.358 align:middle line:90%
you'll become unconscious.

00:06:10.358 --> 00:06:12.400 align:middle line:84%
So you have to know how
to change your metabolism

00:06:12.400 --> 00:06:14.080 align:middle line:84%
and change your
brain wave activity

00:06:14.080 --> 00:06:16.540 align:middle line:84%
and become like in
meditative state.

00:06:16.540 --> 00:06:19.870 align:middle line:84%
But the most difficult thing is
to fight the urge to breathe.

00:06:19.870 --> 00:06:23.800 align:middle line:84%
So the level of
carbon dioxide, CO2,

00:06:23.800 --> 00:06:27.280 align:middle line:84%
keeps rising, rising, rising
because you don't exhale.

00:06:27.280 --> 00:06:31.150 align:middle line:84%
So you have nowhere to
put, or store, that CO2.

00:06:31.150 --> 00:06:34.330 align:middle line:84%
So your body becomes
extremely acidic.

00:06:34.330 --> 00:06:37.270 align:middle line:84%
pH drops like [BRGGG],,
like skydiver.

00:06:37.270 --> 00:06:39.490 align:middle line:84%
And it's just very
uncomfortable.

00:06:39.490 --> 00:06:42.190 align:middle line:84%
And you're just lying
there, not moving,

00:06:42.190 --> 00:06:44.410 align:middle line:84%
but it's like you're
running full-out sprint.

00:06:44.410 --> 00:06:45.820 align:middle line:90%
And your legs are burning.

00:06:45.820 --> 00:06:48.010 align:middle line:84%
Everything is just going
crazy in your body.

00:06:48.010 --> 00:06:50.890 align:middle line:84%
So in that sense,
yes, it looks easy,

00:06:50.890 --> 00:06:52.540 align:middle line:84%
in the sense that
you're not moving.

00:06:52.540 --> 00:06:54.010 align:middle line:90%
But inside, your body--

00:06:54.010 --> 00:06:55.272 align:middle line:90%
it's like a volcano.

00:06:55.272 --> 00:06:56.730 align:middle line:84%
There is so much
activity going on,

00:06:56.730 --> 00:06:58.620 align:middle line:90%
and you have to control that.

00:06:58.620 --> 00:07:01.110 align:middle line:84%
So I think that
that dive-- also,

00:07:01.110 --> 00:07:06.190 align:middle line:84%
I did 22.00 to
show a dedication.

00:07:06.190 --> 00:07:08.050 align:middle line:84%
And it's not like some
minute here or there.

00:07:08.050 --> 00:07:12.190 align:middle line:84%
It's like on the mark that
I had set up to reach.

00:07:12.190 --> 00:07:14.890 align:middle line:84%
And I think it also started
maybe a new era in freediving,

00:07:14.890 --> 00:07:17.590 align:middle line:84%
in the sense that there
are many ways to freedive.

00:07:17.590 --> 00:07:21.790 align:middle line:84%
There are many ways to
demonstrate human skills

00:07:21.790 --> 00:07:24.260 align:middle line:90%
and human limitations.

00:07:24.260 --> 00:07:27.970 align:middle line:84%
And when doctors say, oh,
you'll have brain damage,

00:07:27.970 --> 00:07:30.280 align:middle line:84%
so you'll die after a few
minutes-- there are so

00:07:30.280 --> 00:07:33.760 align:middle line:84%
many things in the
conservative way of looking

00:07:33.760 --> 00:07:38.560 align:middle line:84%
at medical, anatomical,
physiological, neurological

00:07:38.560 --> 00:07:42.430 align:middle line:84%
facts that it really doesn't
add up to what we know today

00:07:42.430 --> 00:07:44.945 align:middle line:84%
when we combine it to the
ancient timeless wisdom.

00:07:44.945 --> 00:07:46.570 align:middle line:84%
And that is one of
my biggest missions,

00:07:46.570 --> 00:07:48.460 align:middle line:90%
is to bridge that gap.

00:07:48.460 --> 00:07:50.830 align:middle line:84%
I come from a
background of biology.

00:07:50.830 --> 00:07:53.200 align:middle line:84%
I have a master's degree in
biology-- marine biologist--

00:07:53.200 --> 00:07:55.660 align:middle line:90%
and I have a PhD in medicine.

00:07:55.660 --> 00:08:00.400 align:middle line:84%
So I know a bit of this world,
but I found it very limiting--

00:08:00.400 --> 00:08:02.320 align:middle line:90%
so limiting-- beliefs.

00:08:02.320 --> 00:08:08.080 align:middle line:84%
And a big part of my "job"
is to break those limits--

00:08:08.080 --> 00:08:11.350 align:middle line:84%
for myself, for humanity,
but also for science--

00:08:11.350 --> 00:08:13.310 align:middle line:90%
to open up for new discoveries.

00:08:13.310 --> 00:08:16.690 align:middle line:84%
And I think when you put
a number right there,

00:08:16.690 --> 00:08:18.680 align:middle line:90%
you can't run away from that.

00:08:18.680 --> 00:08:21.280 align:middle line:84%
No scientist will say
that didn't happen.

00:08:21.280 --> 00:08:22.850 align:middle line:90%
The proof is in the pudding.

00:08:22.850 --> 00:08:27.520 align:middle line:84%
So I think once those
records become more accepted,

00:08:27.520 --> 00:08:32.230 align:middle line:84%
then the idea of
changing the mindset

00:08:32.230 --> 00:08:34.570 align:middle line:84%
and reaching things we
never thought were possible

00:08:34.570 --> 00:08:36.544 align:middle line:90%
also becomes more acceptable.

00:08:36.544 --> 00:08:38.169 align:middle line:84%
And I guess that's
what it's all about.

00:08:38.169 --> 00:08:39.586 align:middle line:84%
When you want to
break limits, you

00:08:39.586 --> 00:08:41.890 align:middle line:84%
want to change the
mindset of people.

00:08:41.890 --> 00:08:44.440 align:middle line:84%
Scientists or athletes
or everyday people--

00:08:44.440 --> 00:08:47.680 align:middle line:84%
you want to change
their mindset to achieve

00:08:47.680 --> 00:08:50.530 align:middle line:90%
greater results in life.

00:08:50.530 --> 00:08:54.860 align:middle line:84%
And with this dive,
the 22 minutes,

00:08:54.860 --> 00:08:56.500 align:middle line:84%
I had my brother
there-- right there.

00:08:56.500 --> 00:08:57.070 align:middle line:90%
He's a doctor.

00:08:57.070 --> 00:08:58.060 align:middle line:90%
He's taken care of me.

00:08:58.060 --> 00:09:01.880 align:middle line:90%
Never freedive alone in water.

00:09:01.880 --> 00:09:03.640 align:middle line:84%
But also to be
there with someone

00:09:03.640 --> 00:09:07.560 align:middle line:84%
who loves you and supports
you and have that experience

00:09:07.560 --> 00:09:09.090 align:middle line:90%
is also very rewarding to me.

00:09:09.090 --> 00:09:13.122 align:middle line:84%
It's not just the number,
because a number is just--

00:09:13.122 --> 00:09:14.830 align:middle line:84%
somebody will beat
the record eventually.

00:09:14.830 --> 00:09:16.330 align:middle line:90%
It's not a big deal.

00:09:16.330 --> 00:09:17.300 align:middle line:90%
It's just a number.

00:09:17.300 --> 00:09:19.830 align:middle line:84%
It's more the experience
in itself that's wonderful.

00:09:19.830 --> 00:09:21.660 align:middle line:84%
And it opens this
dialogue with science.

00:09:21.660 --> 00:09:22.840 align:middle line:90%
Right?

00:09:22.840 --> 00:09:26.290 align:middle line:84%
Next week, I'm speaking at
the American Association

00:09:26.290 --> 00:09:27.673 align:middle line:90%
for Respiratory Care.

00:09:27.673 --> 00:09:28.840 align:middle line:90%
I'm a keynote speaker there.

00:09:28.840 --> 00:09:32.200 align:middle line:84%
I'm actually giving a keynote
that they get credit for--

00:09:32.200 --> 00:09:33.710 align:middle line:90%
continuous educational credit.

00:09:33.710 --> 00:09:35.470 align:middle line:84%
So this would
never have happened

00:09:35.470 --> 00:09:37.830 align:middle line:84%
had I not done this 22-minute
Guinness World Record.

00:09:37.830 --> 00:09:42.180 align:middle line:84%
So in that sense, it's
"proof" that it does matter,

00:09:42.180 --> 00:09:44.680 align:middle line:84%
and when you put yourself on
the line and make these records

00:09:44.680 --> 00:09:48.730 align:middle line:84%
it actually opens the world for
new, amazing things to happen,

00:09:48.730 --> 00:09:50.830 align:middle line:84%
and then, again,
reflects back, hopefully,

00:09:50.830 --> 00:09:54.790 align:middle line:84%
on everyday people-- health,
nutrition, life, mindset,

00:09:54.790 --> 00:10:01.810 align:middle line:84%
and ways to treat patients
and illness from a little bit

00:10:01.810 --> 00:10:03.534 align:middle line:90%
different perspective.

