What does that mean?

00:32:28.390 --> 00:32:31.130 align:middle line:84%
It means that the brain has
many different frequencies.

00:32:31.130 --> 00:32:33.880 align:middle line:84%
It operates at different
electrical levels.

00:32:33.880 --> 00:32:37.270 align:middle line:84%
So alpha state is the dream
state, the flow state,

00:32:37.270 --> 00:32:40.000 align:middle line:84%
where you want to go if
you have peak performance

00:32:40.000 --> 00:32:42.040 align:middle line:84%
and want to take it
to the next level.

00:32:42.040 --> 00:32:44.470 align:middle line:84%
You can also have beta, which
is awareness-- when you're

00:32:44.470 --> 00:32:46.870 align:middle line:84%
listening, when you're
analyzing things,

00:32:46.870 --> 00:32:48.580 align:middle line:90%
that's the normal situation.

00:32:48.580 --> 00:32:50.950 align:middle line:84%
And you have other
frequencies in the higher

00:32:50.950 --> 00:32:53.110 align:middle line:90%
states of meditation.

00:32:53.110 --> 00:32:57.550 align:middle line:84%
But from breathwork alone, you
can take control of your mind.

00:32:57.550 --> 00:33:00.370 align:middle line:90%
So that is the secret of yoga.

00:33:00.370 --> 00:33:04.290 align:middle line:84%
The secret of yoga is that
you quiet those monkeys.

00:33:04.290 --> 00:33:07.360 align:middle line:84%
In Indian traditions, they
talk about the monkey mind.

00:33:07.360 --> 00:33:10.050 align:middle line:84%
So the monkey mind is like
a little wild teenager.

00:33:10.050 --> 00:33:11.050 align:middle line:90%
It's running everywhere.

00:33:11.050 --> 00:33:12.280 align:middle line:90%
And it's true.

00:33:12.280 --> 00:33:15.280 align:middle line:84%
It's very difficult for anyone,
no matter your training,

00:33:15.280 --> 00:33:16.870 align:middle line:90%
to control your mind.

00:33:16.870 --> 00:33:20.470 align:middle line:84%
It's very difficult. We have
so many inputs all the time.

00:33:20.470 --> 00:33:22.030 align:middle line:84%
That's what you
learn in meditation--

00:33:22.030 --> 00:33:25.750 align:middle line:84%
to focus and to cut those inputs
out, or take the inputs in

00:33:25.750 --> 00:33:30.370 align:middle line:84%
and accept them, so they
become just omnipresent,

00:33:30.370 --> 00:33:32.930 align:middle line:84%
but it's not a
disturbing element.

00:33:32.930 --> 00:33:34.870 align:middle line:84%
But from breathing,
you can actually

00:33:34.870 --> 00:33:40.780 align:middle line:84%
start to change the way the
brain is thinking and moving.

00:33:40.780 --> 00:33:46.090 align:middle line:84%
So it's from a physical control
to a neurological control

00:33:46.090 --> 00:33:50.290 align:middle line:84%
to a mental control to
a spiritual control.

00:33:50.290 --> 00:33:53.800 align:middle line:84%
So that progression
is the path of yoga.

00:33:53.800 --> 00:33:55.840 align:middle line:90%
You go from physicality.

00:33:55.840 --> 00:33:56.860 align:middle line:90%
Those are called asanas.

00:33:56.860 --> 00:33:58.780 align:middle line:90%
So it's like a workout--

00:33:58.780 --> 00:33:59.740 align:middle line:90%
body work.

00:33:59.740 --> 00:34:02.115 align:middle line:84%
Then you become more flexible
in your knees, your joints.

00:34:02.115 --> 00:34:03.790 align:middle line:90%
You can sit in the Lotus pose.

00:34:03.790 --> 00:34:05.860 align:middle line:84%
And the reason why
you want to do this,

00:34:05.860 --> 00:34:07.510 align:middle line:90%
it's exactly the same reason.

00:34:07.510 --> 00:34:11.110 align:middle line:84%
You do not want to be
distracted in your mind.

00:34:11.110 --> 00:34:13.179 align:middle line:84%
So if you move your body,
there is a distraction

00:34:13.179 --> 00:34:14.469 align:middle line:90%
because it's called feedback.

00:34:14.469 --> 00:34:17.489 align:middle line:84%
The brain tells these
muscles to move,

00:34:17.489 --> 00:34:19.810 align:middle line:84%
but the muscle is
then sending a signal

00:34:19.810 --> 00:34:20.980 align:middle line:90%
back-- yeah, yeah, got that.

00:34:20.980 --> 00:34:21.760 align:middle line:90%
Yup.

00:34:21.760 --> 00:34:22.420 align:middle line:90%
I moved.

00:34:22.420 --> 00:34:23.962 align:middle line:84%
And the brain says,
OK, that's great.

00:34:23.962 --> 00:34:27.010 align:middle line:84%
Then just stay there until
you do another movement.

00:34:27.010 --> 00:34:28.900 align:middle line:84%
But if you move, you
have distraction.

00:34:28.900 --> 00:34:33.238 align:middle line:84%
So in meditation, it's all
about sitting still for hours.

00:34:33.238 --> 00:34:35.530 align:middle line:84%
But you cannot do that if
you don't have a strong back,

00:34:35.530 --> 00:34:37.072 align:middle line:84%
if you're not flexible
in your knees,

00:34:37.072 --> 00:34:38.739 align:middle line:90%
if you can't open your hips.

00:34:38.739 --> 00:34:43.190 align:middle line:84%
So all those things,
it's just basic workout.

00:34:43.190 --> 00:34:45.690 align:middle line:84%
And that's where, when you've
seen fitness centers and gyms,

00:34:45.690 --> 00:34:47.232 align:middle line:84%
you have yoga, all
this-- it's great.

00:34:47.232 --> 00:34:51.929 align:middle line:84%
It's better than not
doing work with the body,

00:34:51.929 --> 00:34:54.360 align:middle line:84%
but it's very primitive,
because you're

00:34:54.360 --> 00:34:57.120 align:middle line:84%
disconnected from your mind
and from the spiritual aspect.

00:34:57.120 --> 00:34:58.140 align:middle line:90%
But it's still OK.

00:34:58.140 --> 00:34:59.190 align:middle line:90%
It's a beginning.

00:34:59.190 --> 00:35:01.660 align:middle line:84%
Then you move into
higher levels.

00:35:01.660 --> 00:35:03.165 align:middle line:90%
So those are the more ethical.

00:35:03.165 --> 00:35:06.350 align:middle line:90%


00:35:06.350 --> 00:35:11.820 align:middle line:84%
The levels above the physical
level are more ethics--

00:35:11.820 --> 00:35:14.940 align:middle line:84%
so how you treat other people,
how you treat yourself,

00:35:14.940 --> 00:35:16.740 align:middle line:90%
that you're kind to yourself.

00:35:16.740 --> 00:35:18.180 align:middle line:90%
Yama, niyama.

00:35:18.180 --> 00:35:20.220 align:middle line:84%
And then you move
into the fourth step

00:35:20.220 --> 00:35:23.290 align:middle line:84%
