00:59:57.070 --> 01:00:02.630 align:middle line:84%
So gratitude, thankfulness,
and then of course movement.

01:00:02.630 --> 01:00:03.490 align:middle line:90%
Gymnastics.

01:00:03.490 --> 01:00:04.640 align:middle line:90%
Walking.

01:00:04.640 --> 01:00:06.740 align:middle line:84%
Simple things, but just
taking care of your body.

01:00:06.740 --> 01:00:10.160 align:middle line:90%


01:00:10.160 --> 01:00:14.390 align:middle line:84%
And this is timeless wisdom,
even from the Greeks.

01:00:14.390 --> 01:00:17.770 align:middle line:90%


01:00:17.770 --> 01:00:20.100 align:middle line:84%
A healthy body and
a healthy mind.

01:00:20.100 --> 01:00:22.590 align:middle line:84%
It's all connected and we
need to take care of both.

01:00:22.590 --> 01:00:25.290 align:middle line:84%
And that's the disconnect
that maybe in modern times,

01:00:25.290 --> 01:00:28.455 align:middle line:84%
that we are not so connected
to the mind and especially not

01:00:28.455 --> 01:00:31.650 align:middle line:90%
to the spiritual aspects.

01:00:31.650 --> 01:00:40.290 align:middle line:84%
So it's about being passionate
about being given, and fighting

01:00:40.290 --> 01:00:48.047 align:middle line:84%
for, your possibility
of living your dreams.

01:00:48.047 --> 01:00:49.130 align:middle line:90%
So I always loved animals.

01:00:49.130 --> 01:00:50.900 align:middle line:84%
I wanted to grow up
to become a biologist.

01:00:50.900 --> 01:00:54.650 align:middle line:84%
I was lucky that I was born
in a country where education

01:00:54.650 --> 01:00:57.830 align:middle line:84%
is free, and I was lucky
that my grandmother helped me

01:00:57.830 --> 01:00:59.190 align:middle line:90%
with my studies, and my mother.

01:00:59.190 --> 01:01:06.170 align:middle line:84%
And so it's about environment,
and it's about being thankful

01:01:06.170 --> 01:01:10.620 align:middle line:90%
and being a dreamer.

01:01:10.620 --> 01:01:18.860 align:middle line:84%
And I think when we start to
come back to our bodies, that's

01:01:18.860 --> 01:01:19.660 align:middle line:90%
the first step.

01:01:19.660 --> 01:01:22.530 align:middle line:84%
Then we start to understand
how we can affect the heart,

01:01:22.530 --> 01:01:26.430 align:middle line:84%
and then we understand love
on a deeper perspective.

01:01:26.430 --> 01:01:29.640 align:middle line:84%
Because your heart shines
this energy around you.

01:01:29.640 --> 01:01:30.600 align:middle line:90%
We have these auras.

01:01:30.600 --> 01:01:33.750 align:middle line:84%
All tradition have
an aura, whether it's

01:01:33.750 --> 01:01:36.180 align:middle line:84%
Jesus with the halo,
whether it's the Buddha,

01:01:36.180 --> 01:01:37.920 align:middle line:84%
we always have
something above here.

01:01:37.920 --> 01:01:41.330 align:middle line:84%
So something, an
energy, around us.

01:01:41.330 --> 01:01:43.960 align:middle line:90%
So a charisma or aura.

01:01:43.960 --> 01:01:45.920 align:middle line:84%
There are many names,
but this energy

01:01:45.920 --> 01:01:49.100 align:middle line:84%
that transcends the
body, the limitations

01:01:49.100 --> 01:01:51.370 align:middle line:90%
of our physical body.

01:01:51.370 --> 01:01:56.410 align:middle line:84%
And it's so simple to
me, even though I'm

01:01:56.410 --> 01:01:59.650 align:middle line:84%
a scientist, that there
is so much more to life.

01:01:59.650 --> 01:02:02.260 align:middle line:84%
Because I could
challenge any scientist

01:02:02.260 --> 01:02:03.970 align:middle line:90%
and say, OK, so are you married?

01:02:03.970 --> 01:02:05.200 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

01:02:05.200 --> 01:02:08.183 align:middle line:84%
If it's a man, if he's married
to a woman, I would say,

01:02:08.183 --> 01:02:09.100 align:middle line:90%
do you love your wife?

01:02:09.100 --> 01:02:09.900 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

01:02:09.900 --> 01:02:10.930 align:middle line:90%
All right.

01:02:10.930 --> 01:02:12.520 align:middle line:90%
Show me the formula.

01:02:12.520 --> 01:02:14.170 align:middle line:84%
I want to see the
formula for love.

01:02:14.170 --> 01:02:14.970 align:middle line:90%
You know?

01:02:14.970 --> 01:02:16.000 align:middle line:90%
There is no formula.

01:02:16.000 --> 01:02:17.000 align:middle line:90%
I want to see the proof.

01:02:17.000 --> 01:02:22.030 align:middle line:84%
I want to see the
measurements for love.

01:02:22.030 --> 01:02:25.680 align:middle line:84%
And he would probably
say, uh, yeah,

01:02:25.680 --> 01:02:27.490 align:middle line:84%
I don't have those
measurements yet.

01:02:27.490 --> 01:02:29.290 align:middle line:90%
I didn't do those lab studies.

01:02:29.290 --> 01:02:33.430 align:middle line:84%
My point being that there are so
many energies and so much power

01:02:33.430 --> 01:02:37.640 align:middle line:84%
and so much connection
on many levels

01:02:37.640 --> 01:02:39.500 align:middle line:84%
that are just
difficult to measure.

01:02:39.500 --> 01:02:42.290 align:middle line:84%
But it doesn't mean that
they're not existing.

01:02:42.290 --> 01:02:44.150 align:middle line:90%
And love, of course--

01:02:44.150 --> 01:02:45.860 align:middle line:84%
everything is about
love-- to yourself,

01:02:45.860 --> 01:02:49.700 align:middle line:84%
towards animals, towards
nature, being kind-natured.

01:02:49.700 --> 01:02:54.510 align:middle line:84%
And from breathwork
and from meditation,

01:02:54.510 --> 01:02:56.510 align:middle line:84%
you have that direct
connection with your heart.

01:02:56.510 --> 01:02:58.635 align:middle line:84%
And I think that's one of
the strongest things I've

01:02:58.635 --> 01:03:00.838 align:middle line:84%
learned when I started
freediving, is that when you

01:03:00.838 --> 01:03:02.630 align:middle line:84%
hold your breath, there
is something called

01:03:02.630 --> 01:03:03.870 align:middle line:90%
the mammalian dive response.

01:03:03.870 --> 01:03:05.870 align:middle line:84%
So it's a reflex
all people have.

01:03:05.870 --> 01:03:08.510 align:middle line:84%
It's not just freedivers,
but freedivers

01:03:08.510 --> 01:03:10.580 align:middle line:90%
learn to tap into this reflex.

01:03:10.580 --> 01:03:14.120 align:middle line:84%
And what it does is the
heart rate lowers quickly,

01:03:14.120 --> 01:03:17.220 align:middle line:84%
the mind settles, and the
body kind of shuts down,

01:03:17.220 --> 01:03:18.732 align:middle line:90%
so you go into idle.

01:03:18.732 --> 01:03:20.150 align:middle line:90%
Wooo.

01:03:20.150 --> 01:03:22.760 align:middle line:84%
And that's where there's time
for reflection for bigger

01:03:22.760 --> 01:03:25.910 align:middle line:84%
things and for
bigger performances,

01:03:25.910 --> 01:03:29.990 align:middle line:84%
because the body can do things
that under normal circumstances

01:03:29.990 --> 01:03:33.080 align:middle line:90%
it cannot do.

01:03:33.080 --> 01:03:38.240 align:middle line:84%
So what I try is to bring
those reflexes on the forefront

01:03:38.240 --> 01:03:40.435 align:middle line:84%
to people and say, hey,
if you breathe and breathe

01:03:40.435 --> 01:03:41.810 align:middle line:84%
into your heart,
you can actually

01:03:41.810 --> 01:03:42.590 align:middle line:90%
control your heart rate.

01:03:42.590 --> 01:03:43.020 align:middle line:90%
Really?

01:03:43.020 --> 01:03:43.820 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

01:03:43.820 --> 01:03:45.050 align:middle line:90%
Look at your little device.

01:03:45.050 --> 01:03:47.960 align:middle line:84%
Everyone has a little variable
today on a smartphone.

01:03:47.960 --> 01:03:49.887 align:middle line:90%
And then you can see it.

01:03:49.887 --> 01:03:51.470 align:middle line:84%
And it's the same
with breath holding.

01:03:51.470 --> 01:03:54.805 align:middle line:90%
Just hold your breath.

01:03:54.805 --> 01:03:57.180 align:middle line:84%
And after a while, the heart
starts to beat more slowly--

01:03:57.180 --> 01:03:58.830 align:middle line:90%
it's called bradycardia--

01:03:58.830 --> 01:04:01.170 align:middle line:84%
because the body
wants to save oxygen.

01:04:01.170 --> 01:04:03.020 align:middle line:84%
So we have all these
wonderful things.

01:04:03.020 --> 01:04:05.850 align:middle line:84%
I think our body, it's
the most amazing thing.

01:04:05.850 --> 01:04:07.590 align:middle line:84%
You know, combined
with the mind.

01:04:07.590 --> 01:04:09.420 align:middle line:84%
And with the breath,
we have direct access

01:04:09.420 --> 01:04:10.440 align:middle line:90%
to all our organs.

01:04:10.440 --> 01:04:12.450 align:middle line:84%
That's also one of
the secrets of yoga.

01:04:12.450 --> 01:04:15.190 align:middle line:84%
You can tap into the
parasympathetic nervous system.

01:04:15.190 --> 01:04:16.690 align:middle line:84%
Meaning, you can
go into your heart.

01:04:16.690 --> 01:04:20.850 align:middle line:84%
You can travel-- not just
visualize your travel,

01:04:20.850 --> 01:04:24.450 align:middle line:84%
but you can literally travel
from the breath into the nerve

01:04:24.450 --> 01:04:26.720 align:middle line:84%
and connect with that
wire into your heart.

01:04:26.720 --> 01:04:28.470 align:middle line:84%
And when I hold my
breath for a long time,

01:04:28.470 --> 01:04:30.420 align:middle line:84%
I change the way the
heart is beating.

01:04:30.420 --> 01:04:31.440 align:middle line:90%
Not just the pulse.

01:04:31.440 --> 01:04:32.910 align:middle line:84%
That's a primitive,
scientific way

01:04:32.910 --> 01:04:36.630 align:middle line:84%
of looking at the
heart-- the pulse.

01:04:36.630 --> 01:04:38.890 align:middle line:84%
Much more important is the
heart rate variability.

01:04:38.890 --> 01:04:41.970 align:middle line:84%
So how is the change
of beats in the heart?

01:04:41.970 --> 01:04:43.100 align:middle line:90%
And even more importantly--

01:04:43.100 --> 01:04:47.460 align:middle line:84%
I talked with an
Italian heart surgeon.

01:04:47.460 --> 01:04:48.615 align:middle line:90%
He's a freediver.

01:04:48.615 --> 01:04:50.490 align:middle line:84%
He said, if you tell
people what you tell me,

01:04:50.490 --> 01:04:52.590 align:middle line:84%
people will tell
you you're crazy.

01:04:52.590 --> 01:04:54.670 align:middle line:84%
Because when I hold my
breath for a long time,

01:04:54.670 --> 01:04:56.003 align:middle line:90%
I have a dialogue with my heart.

01:04:56.003 --> 01:04:58.660 align:middle line:90%


01:04:58.660 --> 01:04:59.500 align:middle line:90%
I don't demand.

01:04:59.500 --> 01:05:04.520 align:middle line:84%
I just kindly ask,
could you, just

01:05:04.520 --> 01:05:07.910 align:middle line:84%
for a few minutes, 20 minutes
maybe, beat a little bit more

01:05:07.910 --> 01:05:09.180 align:middle line:90%
softly?

01:05:09.180 --> 01:05:13.780 align:middle line:90%
Could you just relax completely?

01:05:13.780 --> 01:05:15.520 align:middle line:84%
And I feel that
shift in the heart.

01:05:15.520 --> 01:05:18.130 align:middle line:84%
It opens up and
it becomes softer.

01:05:18.130 --> 01:05:21.280 align:middle line:84%
And from going from
[FAST PUFFS],, [FAST PUFFS],,

01:05:21.280 --> 01:05:28.412 align:middle line:84%
[FAST PUFFS],, it goes to
[SLOW PUFFS],, [SLOW PUFFS],,

01:05:28.412 --> 01:05:31.310 align:middle line:90%
[SLOW PUFFS].

01:05:31.310 --> 01:05:33.590 align:middle line:84%
That saves oxygen.
It saves brainpower.

01:05:33.590 --> 01:05:38.320 align:middle line:84%
Saves basically
everything in your energy

01:05:38.320 --> 01:05:39.790 align:middle line:84%
so you can hold
your breath longer.

01:05:39.790 --> 01:05:41.540 align:middle line:84%
And you can do that
in all things in life.

01:05:41.540 --> 01:05:43.660 align:middle line:84%
So I try to bring the
breath holding part in,

01:05:43.660 --> 01:05:45.410 align:middle line:84%
which in pranayama is
also very important,

01:05:45.410 --> 01:05:48.440 align:middle line:84%
but it's forgotten in
normal, modern "yoga."

01:05:48.440 --> 01:05:52.670 align:middle line:84%
So I try to bring both
sides of the coin to people

01:05:52.670 --> 01:05:55.250 align:middle line:84%
and give them choices
to actually use this

01:05:55.250 --> 01:05:56.570 align:middle line:90%
in an everyday life situation.

