to be, first of all,

01:07:58.650 --> 01:08:00.240 align:middle line:90%
conscious about breathing.

01:08:00.240 --> 01:08:02.970 align:middle line:84%
Second of all, use the nose
because you want that nitrogen

01:08:02.970 --> 01:08:05.910 align:middle line:84%
oxide-- you want that extra
molecule that people have--

01:08:05.910 --> 01:08:09.730 align:middle line:84%
to actually make more
oxygen jump into your lungs

01:08:09.730 --> 01:08:12.870 align:middle line:84%
because the alveoli, the blood
vascular system in the lungs,

01:08:12.870 --> 01:08:15.420 align:middle line:84%
open more when you
breathe with your nose.

01:08:15.420 --> 01:08:16.979 align:middle line:84%
And then when they
do a slow exhale,

01:08:16.979 --> 01:08:19.029 align:middle line:90%
they tap into the vagus nerve.

01:08:19.029 --> 01:08:22.770 align:middle line:84%
So when people breathe what
I call 1, 2 breathing--

01:08:22.770 --> 01:08:27.390 align:middle line:90%
the ratio of 1 to 2--

01:08:27.390 --> 01:08:32.160 align:middle line:84%
so 1 to 2 is just one inhalation
is, for example, four seconds.

01:08:32.160 --> 01:08:34.146 align:middle line:90%
[INHALES]

01:08:34.146 --> 01:08:35.479 align:middle line:90%
And then there's a slight pause.

01:08:35.479 --> 01:08:36.762 align:middle line:90%
This is very important.

01:08:36.762 --> 01:08:38.470 align:middle line:84%
And then there's an
exhale for 8 seconds,

01:08:38.470 --> 01:08:40.796 align:middle line:90%
so the double amount of time.

01:08:40.796 --> 01:08:41.782 align:middle line:90%
[EXHALES]

01:08:41.782 --> 01:08:47.679 align:middle line:90%


01:08:47.679 --> 01:08:48.479 align:middle line:90%
And a pause again.

01:08:48.479 --> 01:08:50.979 align:middle line:84%
And then your body tells you
to breathe and you start again.

01:08:50.979 --> 01:08:52.629 align:middle line:90%
[INHALES]

01:08:52.629 --> 01:08:55.330 align:middle line:84%
And the breathing comes from
the belly, from the diaphragm.

01:08:55.330 --> 01:08:59.050 align:middle line:84%
You're just completely
relaxing the shoulders.

01:08:59.050 --> 01:09:02.319 align:middle line:84%
Your lower jaw is dropping
down a little bit.

01:09:02.319 --> 01:09:06.160 align:middle line:84%
Your tongue falls to the bottom
of the floor of the mouth.

01:09:06.160 --> 01:09:09.279 align:middle line:84%
Your eyes and your
forehead relax.

01:09:09.279 --> 01:09:11.290 align:middle line:84%
And that translate
quickly into your brain.

01:09:11.290 --> 01:09:12.868 align:middle line:90%
And then you exhale again.

01:09:12.868 --> 01:09:19.880 align:middle line:84%
[EXHALES] So 1, 2 breathing,
conscious breathing,

01:09:19.880 --> 01:09:25.015 align:middle line:84%
it's the best way to conquer
any stressful situation in life.

